# Next.js & Auth Patterns

Read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before assuming Next.js APIs — this project uses Next.js 16 with breaking changes.

## Stack

- Better Auth: config in `features/auth/server/auth.ts`, API route `app/api/auth/[...all]/route.ts`.
- Session helpers: `features/auth/lib/session.ts` (`getServerSession`, `hasPermission`).
- Client: `features/auth/client/auth-client.ts`.
- Prisma client: `@/lib/prisma` (singleton with adapter).

## Auth rules

- No public registration — users created via admin (`features/auth/services/create-user.ts`).
- Login: username **or** email (`features/auth/actions/sign-in.ts`).
- Check permissions with `hasPermission(session, "permission_name")` — do not hardcode roles in UI.
- Scope operational data by `subdomain_id` / `getActiveSubdomainId(session)` when building Domain 2+.

## Server actions

- Put `redirect()` **outside** `try/catch` (it throws internally).
- Better Auth from server actions needs `nextCookies()` plugin (already in auth config).

## Env

- `BETTER_AUTH_SECRET`, `BETTER_AUTH_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_BETTER_AUTH_URL`, `DATABASE_URL`.
